  "about": "I am a highly organized and detail-oriented Credit Control Senior Analyst with over four years of professional experience. Currently I work at Napco National, I excel in optimizing accounts receivable processes and building strong relationships with customers to ensure timely payments.\n\nIn my role, I manage the entire accounts receivable aging process, conduct quarterly customer balance confirmations, and oversee the approval of orders based on credit terms. I ensure compliance with statutory and company requirements while following up on outstanding invoices and uncollected receivables.\n\nI am adept at analyzing and reconciling accounts receivable data, creating reports for management, and resolving any discrepancies. My expertise in financial analysis and strategic thinking has enabled me to effectively reduce credit risk and maintain accurate financial records.\n\nI hold a Bachelor's degree in Finance from the University of Indianapolis and am an associate member of the Saudi Organization for Certified Public Accountants (SOCPA). I am currently pursuing my Certified Management Accountant designation to further enhance my skills.\n\nI am passionate about leveraging my skills in Zakat & Tax, Accounting, and Auditing to contribute to financial success. I welcome opportunities to connect with fellow professionals and explore potential collaborations. Feel free to reach out via email at almodhih.1995@gmail.com.",
