      "jobDescription": "1. Accounting and Financial Records:\n   - Oversee daily accounting operations and ensure proper documentation of all financial transactions.\n   - Conduct monthly and annual account closures according to accepted accounting standards.\n   - Monitor expenses and revenues to ensure alignment with the budget.\n2. Financial Planning and Budgeting:\n   - Lead the process of preparing budgets, financial statements, and annual financial plans, collaborating with department managers and section heads.\n   - Monitor expenses and revenues and ensure compliance with policies and regulations.\n   - Manage cash flows and ensure adequate liquidity for operations.\n   - Lead the team, monitor performance, and develop their skills.\n   - Develop financial policies and procedures and monitor compliance.\n   - Create financial plans aligned with the association's strategic goals.\n   - Provide financial forecasts and recommendations to executive management.\n3. Financial Reporting:\n   - Prepare and analyze financial data and monthly and periodic reports.\n   - Ensure compliance with zakat, tax regulations, and approved accounting systems in the Kingdom.\n4. Compliance and Auditing:\n   - Coordinate with internal and external auditors to ensure financial transparency and compliance.\n   - Implement effective internal controls and update financial policies as needed.\n5. Grants and Financial Support:\n   - Manage financial aspects related to supported projects and financial grants.\n6. Payroll and Employee Support:\n   - Supervise accurate and timely payroll processing.\n   - Coordinate with the HR department to ensure compliance with payroll and benefits policies.\n7. Supervision and Inventory Management:\n   - Oversee and conduct annual and quarterly inventories of equipment in warehouses, as well as the association's assets in collaboration with other departments.",
